<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
<a class="spoiler" href="/questions/2019680-the-story-that-love-tells-about-her">This question contains spoilers...</a>
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[The story that Love tells about her father... She was raped as a child, and vowed to never marry in order to never have sex. But she agrees to marry Will's grandfather who is (1) much older than her, (2) her boss and in a position of power, and (3) would be alone in the house with her. I know she wanted her own property, but I would think the risks in a faux-marriage would be too high for her. Anyone else? <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
