<span id="freeTextContainer227835583204474577">I can&apos;t believe Janette only gave this book 3 stars! I love this book, it&apos;s so delightful, the characters are so human with their fears, and pettiness and prejudices and lusts. It had a lot of humor in it as well, like when the grandpa decided eloped with the millner (hat maker) 2 weeks after the grandma died, and his excuse was, &quot;she&apos;s as dead as she&apos;s ever gonna be!&quot; But we didn&apos;t doubt his devotion to the grandma, because he completely lined her grave with cut roses from her rose garden. It&apos;s</span>
